   Research Interests:

   We are studying DNA damage and repair in people and in higher plants.
   Major areas are:
    1. DNA repair, including photorepair, in human skin and white blood
       cells.
    2. Ultraviolet and sunlight-induced damage to higher plants, including
       alfalfa, rice, and soybean, and the ability of these plants to
       repair such damage.
    3. Damage to DNA by heavy ions, including restoration of DNA damages
       by mammalian cells.
     __________________________________________________________________

